---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
// Placeholder for dynamic blog post pages
// Will be wired to content collections later
---

<BaseLayout title="Blog Post" currentPath="/blog/">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-12 py-12">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span
          class="bg-[var(--color-primary-container)]/10 text-[var(--color-primary-container)] text-[10px] font-bold px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest"
          >Deep Dive</span
        >
        <span class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-outline)] font-mono"
          >2024-10-08</span
        >
      </div>
      <h1
        class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-tight mb-6"
      >
        The Cost of 1ms: Latency in Lithography Control Systems
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-on-surface-variant)] text-lg">
        Exploring the non-linear cost of latency in high-precision EUV
        manufacturing and why nanosecond-level optimization matters.
      </p>
    </header>
    <div
      class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none text-[var(--color-on-surface-variant)]"
    >
      <p>
        In the world of EUV lithography, every millisecond counts. When you're
        etching circuits at the 3nm node, the margin for error isn't just small
        — it's nearly non-existent. This post explores why latency optimization
        at the sub-millisecond level is the single most impactful engineering
        challenge in modern chip manufacturing.
      </p>
      <h2
        class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-on-surface)] mt-12 mb-4"
      >
        The Physics of Precision
      </h2>
      <p>
        EUV light travels at just under 300,000 km/s. In the 1ms it takes for a
        control signal to propagate, the wafer stage has already moved
        micrometers. This is the fundamental tension: software must be faster
        than physics.
      </p>
      <div
        class="my-8 p-6 bg-[var(--color-surface-container-low)] rounded-lg ghost-border"
      >
        <code class="text-[var(--color-primary-container)] text-sm font-mono"
          >// Critical path: 248μs budget for the complete control loop<br />
          // Stage position → Sensor read → Compute → Actuate<br />
          constexpr auto CONTROL_BUDGET = 248us;</code
        >
      </div>
      <p>
        The article continues with deep analysis of control loop architectures,
        real-time operating system considerations, and hardware-software
        co-design patterns that enable sub-microsecond response times...
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--color-outline-variant)]/10">
      <a
        href="/blog/"
        class="text-[var(--color-primary-container)] text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2 hover:gap-4 transition-all"
      >
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-sm">arrow_back</span>
        Back to All Articles
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
